      "lineNbr": 108,
      "author": {
        "id": 1333728
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-04T22:04:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the best practice that any sort of recoverable error should be handled by the server and not reported at all? Then it would make sense to shut down on first error.\n\nIn particular, I was thinking that connection handlers could report their errors on this channel too, and that we might want to allow the server to keep running in that case. But maybe it makes more sense to just fail completely and allow Swarming / some other infrastructure to do a full retry?",
      "parentUuid": "f8aacb23_d78c47d3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 108,
        "startChar": 50,
        "endLine": 108,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "6b6a0892837873ad614239efd435c28409ed0c29",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d7f5481a_0f42041a",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/sink.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 108,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-04T22:44:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "examples of recoverable errors?\n\nearlier we wanted to use the error package as an indication that the server is down. With the possibility of recoverable errors, we no longer can do that. Maybe to make it more explicit, errC should be renamed to Done()?",
      "parentUuid": "e74cb3c8_fb940977",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 108,
        "startChar": 50,
        "endLine": 108,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "6b6a0892837873ad614239efd435c28409ed0c29",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8203cc1f_4558c02e",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/sink.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 108,
      "author": {
        "id": 1333728
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-04T23:15:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"Done()\" should probably be reserved for signaling that the server has come to a graceful shutdown. When we have a real backend to talk to the wrapper will need to wait for all the open connections to flush their data.\n\nRe: recoverable errors, I am thinking of connection level errors. If a client sends an invalid message, what should we do? Do we stop the whole server?\n\nFor now I will assume everything on errC is fatal and if we need a non-fatal channel we can add it later.",
      "parentUuid": "d7f5481a_0f42041a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 108,
        "startChar": 50,
        "endLine": 108,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "6b6a0892837873ad614239efd435c28409ed0c29",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "763efb86_574a9605",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/sink.go",
        "patchSetId": 14
      },
      "lineNbr": 108,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-05T22:48:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e \"Done()\" should probably be reserved for signaling that the server has come to a graceful shutdown. When we have a real backend to talk to the wrapper will need to wait for all the open connections to flush their data.\n\u003e \n\u003e Re: recoverable errors, I am thinking of connection level errors. If a client sends an invalid message, what should we do? Do we stop the whole server?\n\nI think this can be configurable, whether it should shutdown itself. Otherwise, I don\u0027t know what client would do with recoverable errors other than logging them, but that we can do ourselves.\n\n\u003e For now I will assume everything on errC is fatal and if we need a non-fatal channel we can add it later.\n\nsgtm",
      "parentUuid": "8203cc1f_4558c02e",
